   <taskbody>
      <steps class="- topic/ol task/steps ">
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">To manually operate the mixer, use the touch screen on the front door of the mixer cabinet.</cmd>
            <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">
                  <fig class="- topic/fig ">
                     <image href="media/image2.jpg"
                            placement="break"
                            align="center"
                            class="- topic/image "/>
                  </fig>
               </p>
            </info>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">On the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Overview</b> screen, log in and press the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Manual
                  Panel</uicontrol> button.</cmd>
            <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">
               <ul class="- topic/ul ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">When logged in, the operator can place the mixer into Manual mode and operate
                     each piece of equipment individually. </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">After completing work, tap "remote" to tell the mixer to receive commands from
                     the SCADA instead of manually from the HMI.</li>
               </ul>
               <note type="note" class="- topic/note ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">The Manual mode of operation is NOT interlocked! The operator can switch each
                     drive on and off independently from another device. The operator is responsible
                     for maintaining the correct order so that no equipment is damaged.</p>
               </note>
               <p class="- topic/p ">
                  <fig class="- topic/fig ">
                     <image href="media/image3.jpg"
                            placement="break"
                            align="center"
                            class="- topic/image "/>
                  </fig>
               </p>
            </info>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Operate the listed devices by pressing the appropriate buttons.</cmd>
            <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">
               <ul class="- topic/ul ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">Press the<uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol "> Start </uicontrol>and <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Stop </uicontrol>buttons,
                     or <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Open</uicontrol> and <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Close</uicontrol> buttons, to
                     operate a device.</li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">Some devices have a tipping (jog) operation. Press and hold the
                        <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Tipp</uicontrol> button to turn the device on. Release the button
                     to stop the device.  </li>
               </ul>
               <p class="- topic/p ">
                  <fig class="- topic/fig ">
                     <image href="media/image4.jpg"
                            placement="break"
                            align="center"
                            class="- topic/image "/>
                  </fig>
               </p>
            </info>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Press the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">System </uicontrol> button on the bottom of the screen to
               display the System screen.</cmd>
            <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">
               <ul class="- topic/ul ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">DB Lock</b>: This button only has functionality when the panel is connected
                     to the PLC.</li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">User Administration</b>: Opens a screen that displays all active users,
                     where users can change passwords, and new users are added.</li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Transfer</b>: For Zippe-Service only, to transfer program changes to the
                     panel.</li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Show Version</b>: The current version of the touch screen is displayed.</li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">System Diagnostic</b>: Use this screen to browse all connected Profinet
                     devices to check their actual working status.</li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Display Calibration</b>: Used to improve touchscreen accuracy. Follow the
                     instructions on the screen.</li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Display Cleaning</b>: Locks the touchscreen for a few seconds to physically
                     clean the display.</li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Exit Runtime</b>: Click this button to shut down the HMI-Runtime. This is
                     typically done to close the control screen, and access other parts of the touch
                     panel operating system.</li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Control Panel</b>: Opens the control panel of the underlying Windows
                     System.</li>
               </ul>
               <p class="- topic/p ">
                  <fig class="- topic/fig ">
                     <image href="media/image5.jpg"
                            placement="break"
                            align="center"
                            class="- topic/image "/>
                  </fig>
               </p>
            </info>
         </step>
